Data Type:- 
-Fundamental Datatype     - Userdefined Datatype       - Derived Datatype  

1. Fundamental(16-bit machine): 
int(2 byte) , float(4 byte) , char(1 byte) , double(8 byte) , void , long int(4 byte)

# Size of an integer depend on the machine size. 
# Precision of floating type number is 6 digit and for the double number is 14 digit.
# Void type has no value. It generally use for the written type of function.
# The purpose of size operators that the size of particular datatype.

Format specifier:-
1. int - "%d"         2. char - "%c"         3. Float - "%f"         4. double - "%lf"         5. long int - "%ld"

2. Userdefined Datatype:
Enum: Identifier name{value1, value2,..............,valuen}

# The compiler automatically assign integer digits beginning with 0 to all the enumeration constant.

3. Derived Datatype: Array, Sturcture, Union.
Eg: include<stdio.h>
      void main() 
  {
     
      typedef int integer;
      integer a=0;
      printf("%d",a);
     
     } 


